08/15/99
   * Extract and utilize picture metadata, including
     date/time picture was taken, size and depth, etc.
   * Better recovery from transmission errors. Currently,
     errors during large data transfers are handled 
     fairly well, with near 100% recovery. Errors during
     control sequences result is termination of the 
     current command, and probable hung camera.  
     Fortunately, the latter type of error is rare.
	* 'Configure Camera' should set baudrate, pacing,
	  tracing, flash, picture quality, etc., and save 
     these values in ~/.gphoto/konicarc
   * "Autoconfigure" tool to locate the camera and 
     determine optimal baud rate and pacing values.       